title: "Integration: Compression, Distortion, Novelty, and Meaning"
authors:
  - family-names: DiSisto
    given-names: Daniel
type: article
url: "https://github.com/ddisisto/integration-framework"
repository-code: "https://github.com/ddisisto/integration-framework"
license: CC-BY-4.0
version: "0.8"
date-released: "2026-03-28"
abstract: >-
  This paper argues that LLM effectiveness reflects hierarchical
  multi-scale compression, and that the autoregressive loop is
  fundamentally ambivalent — enriching when each token surfaces
  structure unavailable from context, stabilising when tokens
  reinforce existing trajectories. The enrichment fraction over a
  window of generation determines the character of the output and
  is directly measurable via the model's own surprisal.
